Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, kitty
Description: Robust wrapper for kitty terminal emulator with session presets
 kitty-launcher is a Rust-based wrapper for the kitty terminal emulator that
 allows launching terminal sessions with flexible configuration presets.
 .
 Features:
  - Validates input parameters for security
  - Searches for session configuration files in multiple standard locations
  - Provides helpful error messages
  - Launches kitty terminal with the specified session preset
 .
 Configuration search path (in order of priority):
  - ./etc/kitty (current directory)
  - ~/.local/etc/kitty (user home directory)
  - /opt/etc/kitty (optional system-wide)
  - ~/.config/kitty (kitty standard location)
